data.title: Fast Service!!
data.text: Delicious meal in a hurry and friendly customer service near downtown, easy parking and delivery to hotels available.

data.title: Better than some sub shops.  This trip it was inconsistent.
data.text:
As I ate my sandwich, I thought I was eating two different sandwiches.  The first (the end of the bread) was hard, the lettuce had little if any dressing, there was minimal mayo, and a bit light on the meat (supposed to be double meat and cheese).

The second half was totally different.  The bread was fresh and soft, the lettuce had plenty of dressing, there was lots of mayo (maybe too much), and LOTS of meat and cheese.

It seems somebody in being freaky fast, over looked half my sandwich.

data.title: Bland
data.text: Many people rave about Jimmy Johns. The bread is fresh, but flavorless. The meat and toppings are really not much different than Safeway sells. I prefer Safeway. Not sure what about this draws some of the foodies I know. Color me bewildered.

data.title: Typical Jimmy Johns
data.text: Convenient sandwich shop in downtown Kirkland.  Friendly service and good food.  It's greatest asset, besides the sandwiches, is the location in Kirkland.

data.title: Great party platters
data.text: We order and pick up the party platters on our way to events, picnics, boating etc.  Order online and choose 5 sandwiches that they cut into 4 pieces for a 20 piece platter.  Pay online and just pop into the store to pick them up.  Yum

data.title: Ho, hummmm.
data.text: Loud and slightly obnoxious sub shop that has great bread but little else that other can eat.  Sorry, not a fan.

data.title: Good choice for a sandwich if you're in downtown Kirkland
data.text:
Good for a sandwich chain. I like their turkey, and also their avocado spread.
This place is kept *very* clean. I'm not sure if this is part of Jimmy John's identity or just specific to that store but they always have plenty of people working there to take care of the place and ensure prompt service.
Delivery is also seriously quick, no joke sometimes they're up at my house within 10 minutes of the order having been placed.
